    "Fed [80] proposes a sub-consensus framework.",
    "In this framework, traditional cross-entropy training is performed on clients with labeled data.",
    "For clients without labels, a consistency regularization framework, such as mean-teacher, is utilized.",
    "Generally, the global objective function in PC-FSSL can be written as:where the global model aims to minimize a function that is affected by two types of clients: fully-labeled clients, denoted as a, and fully-unlabeled clients, denoted as b.",
    "Specifically, L a represents the supervised task-relevant loss, which differs from L b."
